I’ve had this curtain/sectional project in mind for about 4 months😂 but haven’t had time to bring it to life in the pergola! #ad I booked a Tasker through @taskrabbit to get this project moving! My Tasker assembled the sectional and put up these tension rods with curtains to give this space such an inviting vibe! TaskRabbit is an app that helps you find skilled, reliable Taskers in your area. Previously, I’ve had them do shelf mounting, carpentry, and furniture-assembly!

For my next project I may see if they can repaint the pergola a different color! Any color suggestions??

#LGPartner We decided to reconfigure the laundry room! Changing our washer and dryer to the @lgusa WashTower made space for me to add a little corner for my laundry hamper to roll into and a cabinet above it!

My overall color scheme is pink, white, and green so I was super excited that there was a Nature Green color available. What kind of laundry setup do you have? A stacking unit or side by side units?

Thank you so much to @lgusa for sending me this WashTower!

#LGPartner Spend a day of laundry with me! I love that this new format is so functional. It’s easy for me to roll clothes in here and there’s enough space for me to store everything/do laundry in here!

Laundry days have been made a little quicker now that I’m also using the ThinQ app to manage my 
laundry and see when it’s done. Wrinkly clothes are one of my biggest pet peeves, so I also love 
the TurboSteam feature the WashTower has!

Thank you so much to @lgusa for sending me this WashTower!

*THESE ARE FOR BATTERY OPERATED LED LIGHTS ONLY, NOT REAL ONES WITH A FLAME

The cutest tea light ghosts👻 

1. Take crayola model magic or crayola air dry clay and roll it into a ball then use a rolling pin(mine is only for crafts) or bottle to flatten it out to a circle.

2. Place over a bottle or small jar. I added an Easter egg to the top of mine to get a rounder shape for the head. Pinch the middle to form the ghost.

3. Take a straw to make the eyes!

4. Let them dry and then add battery-operated tea lights underneath! *these aren’t for real tea lights with a flame

I used model magic because to me it was easier to work with, but I also made some with the crayola air dry clay which hardens more while model magic is still soft and flexible!
